Transfer Bot Conversations to Another Bot

Create custom solutions in your org by adopting a multi-bot strategy. Use dialog Rule steps to transfer bot conversations to another bot.

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To build and manage Einstein Bots:
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

Bot-to-bot transfers between standard and enhanced bots arenâ€™t supported. Both bots in a bot-to-bot transfer must be of the same type.

When you create multiple bots, you can transfer conversations from one bot to another. Start with two bots: the source bot and the destination bot. Create an ID variable to define the destination bot.

Create an ID variable:
In the Bot Builder menu, select Variables.
Click New.
For the Data Type, select ID. For the SObject Type, select Bot.
Click Save.

Add a Rule dialog step:
Drag the Set Routing Type onto the canvas.
Select Route Type: Bot
Select Route Source: destination bot
Select Destination Variable: ID variable

Click Add Rule Action:
Select Transfer
Select Destination Variable: ID variable set in previous step

Save the dialog.
title: Transferring Bot Conversations
